text: Cross section of Jonadel, National Fruit Collection (acc. 1963-112) Jonadel is a cultivar of apple which was raised in 1923 at the Iowa Agricultural Experiment Station, Ames, Iowa, United States, a cross between the Jonathan and the Red Delicious. It was introduced in 1958. Jonadel has a green-yellow basic color with a streaked orange covering color. ==External links== * Category:Apple cultivars with patented mutants Category:American apples Category:Apple cultivars
